The paper discusses the use of the restricted isometry property (RIP) in compressed sensing, which is a topic closely related to information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The paper also proposes a bound for the orthogonal matching pursuit (OMP) algorithm, which is a popular algorithm in machine learning (cs.LG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper mentions the sharpness of the bound, which is a topic in mathematical modeling (cs.MM).
